ier series associated with the standard inner product given by the measure µ. No additional conditions are needed.", :doc-id "On Fourier Series of a Discrete Jacobi-Sobolev Inner Product. 2002  ,  ,  "}, 1137192 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1137192, :key "journals/vc/Yukita96", :title "A functional presentation of Fourier series convergence.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1272683, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Shûichi Yukita"}), :year 1996, :venue "The Visual Computer", :ncit 0, :string "A functional presentation of Fourier series convergence.. ", :doc-id "A functional presentation of Fourier series convergence. 1996  "}, 958344 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 958344, :key "journals/jat/BustozC01", :title "Basic Analog of Fourier Series on a q-Linear Grid.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 550481, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Joaquín Bustoz"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 490341, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "José Luis Cardoso"}), :year 2001, :venue "Journal of Approximation Theory", :ncit 21, :string "Basic Analog of Fourier Series on a q-Linear Grid.. ", :doc-id "Basic Analog of Fourier Series on a q-Linear Grid. 2001  ,  "}, 3715593 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3715593, :key "journals/scjapan/TabeiYU91", :title "Backprojection with fourier series expansion and FFT.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 371931, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Makoto Tabei"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 143306, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Hiroshi Yamamoto"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 99397, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mitsuhiro Ueda"}), :year 1991, :venue "Systems and Computers in Japan", :ncit 0, :string "Backprojection with fourier series expansion and FFT.. ", :doc-id "Backprojection with fourier series expansion and FFT. 1991  ,  ,  "}, 869993 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 869993, :key "journals/entcs/Moser08", :title "On the Convergence of Fourier Series of Computable Lebesgue Integrable Functions.", :abstract "This paper studies how well computable functions can be approximated by their Fourier series. To this end, we equip the space of L^p-computable functions (computable Lebesgue integrable functions) with a size notion, by introducing L^p-computable Baire categories. We show that L^p-computable Baire categories satisfy the following three basic properties. Singleton sets {f} (where f is L^p-computable) are meager, suitable infinite unions of meager sets are meager, and the whole space of L^p-computable functions is not meager. We give an alternative characterization of meager sets via Banach Mazur games. We study the convergence of Fourier series for L^p-computable functions and show that whereas for every p>1, the Fourier series of every L^p-computable function f converges to f in the L^p norm, the set of L^1-computable functions whose Fourier series does not diverge almost everywhere is meager.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1454975, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Philippe Moser"}), :year 2008, :venue "Electr. Notes Theor. Comput. Sci.", :ncit 1, :string "On the Convergence of Fourier Series of Computable Lebesgue Integrable Functions.. This paper studies how well computable functions can be approximated by their Fourier series. To this end, we equip the space of L^p-computable functions (computable Lebesgue integrable functions) with a size notion, by introducing L^p-computable Baire categories. We show that L^p-computable Baire categories satisfy the following three basic properties. Singleton sets {f} (where f is L^p-computable) are meager, suitable infinite unions of meager sets are meager, and the whole space of L^p-computable functions is not meager. We give an alternative characterization of meager sets via Banach Mazur games. We study the convergence of Fourier series for L^p-computable functions and show that whereas for every p>1, the Fourier series of every L^p-computable function f converges to f in the L^p norm, the set of L^1-computable functions whose Fourier series does not diverge almost everywhere is meager.", :doc-id "On the Convergence of Fourier Series of Computable Lebesgue Integrable Functions. 2008  "}, 1115977 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1115977, :key "journals/tmi/ChungDSED07", :title "Weighted Fourier Series Representation and Its Application to Quantifying the Amount of Gray Matter.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 161096, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Moo K. Chung"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 476537, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Kim M. Dalton"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 757421, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Li Shen"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 300880, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Alan C. Evans"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1474322, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Richard J. Davidson"}), :year 2007, :venue "IEEE Trans. Med. Imaging", :ncit 60, :string "Weighted Fourier Series Representation and Its Application to Quantifying the Amount of Gray Matter.. ", :doc-id "Weighted Fourier Series Representation and Its Application to Quantifying the Amount of Gray Matter. 2007  ,  ,  ,  ,  "}, 1197897 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1197897, :key "reference/gis/X08mr", :title "Fourier Series.", :abstract nil, :author (), :year 2008, :venue "Encyclopedia of GIS", :ncit 0, :string "Fourier Series.. ", :doc-id "Fourier Series. 2008 "}, 772106 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 772106, :key "journals/cacm/George63b", :title "Remark on algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 438364, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Richard George"}), :year 1963, :venue "Commun. ACM", :ncit 0, :string "Remark on algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation.. ", :doc-id "Remark on algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation. 1963  "}, 958794 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 958794, :key "journals/jat/Suslov02", :title "Some Expansions in Basic Fourier Series and Related Topics.", :abstract "We consider explicit expansions of some elementary and q-functions in basic Fourier series introduced recently by Bustoz and Suslov. Natural q-extensions of the Bernoulli and Euler polynomials, numbers, and the Riemann zeta function are discussed as a by-product.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 530165, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sergei K. Suslov"}), :year 2002, :venue "Journal of Approximation Theory", :ncit 19, :string "Some Expansions in Basic Fourier Series and Related Topics.. We consider explicit expansions of some elementary and q-functions in basic Fourier series introduced recently by Bustoz and Suslov. Natural q-extensions of the Bernoulli and Euler polynomials, numbers, and the Riemann zeta function are discussed as a by-product.", :doc-id "Some Expansions in Basic Fourier Series and Related Topics. 2002  "}, 1226154 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1226154, :key "journals/jscic/KvernadzeHS99", :title "Locating Discontinuities of a Bounded Function by the Partial Sums of Its Fourier Series.", :abstract "A key step for some methods dealing with the reconstruction of a function with jump discontinuities is the accurate approximation of the jumps and their locations. Various methods have been suggested in the literature to obtain this valuable information. In the present paper, we develop an algorithm based on asymptotic expansion formulae obtained in our earlier work. The algorithm enables one to approximate the locations of discontinuities and the magnitudes of jumps of a bounded function given its truncated Fourier series. We investigate the stability of the method and study its complexity. Finally, we consider several numerical examples in order to emphasize strong and weak points of the algorithm.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 345789, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "George Kvernadze"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1171287, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Thomas Hagstrom"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 728034, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Henry Shapiro"}), :year 1999, :venue "J. Sci. Comput.", :ncit 20, :string "Locating Discontinuities of a Bounded Function by the Partial Sums of Its Fourier Series.. A key step for some methods dealing with the reconstruction of a function with jump discontinuities is the accurate approximation of the jumps and their locations. Various methods have been suggested in the literature to obtain this valuable information. In the present paper, we develop an algorithm based on asymptotic expansion formulae obtained in our earlier work. The algorithm enables one to approximate the locations of discontinuities and the magnitudes of jumps of a bounded function given its truncated Fourier series. We investigate the stability of the method and study its complexity. Finally, we consider several numerical examples in order to emphasize strong and weak points of the algorithm.", :doc-id "Locating Discontinuities of a Bounded Function by the Partial Sums of Its Fourier Series. 1999  ,  ,  "}, 3110314 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3110314, :key "journals/ijmmsc/ZhangCQ05", :title "Corrected Fourier series and its application to function approximation.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 655963, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Qing-Hua Zhang"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1132944, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Shuiming Chen"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1344806, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Yuanyuan Qu"}), :year 2005, :venue "Int. J. Math. Mathematical Sciences", :ncit 5, :string "Corrected Fourier series and its application to function approximation.. ", :doc-id "Corrected Fourier series and its application to function approximation. 2005  ,  ,  "}, 869994 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 869994, :key "journals/entcs/MoriYT08", :title "Integral of Fine Computable functions and Walsh Fourier series.", :abstract "We define the effective integrability of Fine-computable functions and effectivize some fundamental limit theorems in the theory of Lebesgue integral such as Bounded Convergence Theorem and Dominated Convergence Theorem. It is also proved that the Walsh-Fourier coefficients of an effectively integrable Fine-computable function form an E-computable sequence of reals and converge effectively to zero. The latter fact is the effectivization of Walsh-Riemann-Lebesgue Theorem. The article is closed with the effective version of Dirichlet's test.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1370348, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Takakazu Mori"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1505236, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mariko Yasugi"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 464740, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Yoshiki Tsujii"}), :year 2008, :venue "Electr. Notes Theor. Comput. Sci.", :ncit 3, :string "Integral of Fine Computable functions and Walsh Fourier series.. We define the effective integrability of Fine-computable functions and effectivize some fundamental limit theorems in the theory of Lebesgue integral such as Bounded Convergence Theorem and Dominated Convergence Theorem. It is also proved that the Walsh-Fourier coefficients of an effectively integrable Fine-computable function form an E-computable sequence of reals and converge effectively to zero. The latter fact is the effectivization of Walsh-Riemann-Lebesgue Theorem. The article is closed with the effective version of Dirichlet's test.", :doc-id "Integral of Fine Computable functions and Walsh Fourier series. 2008  ,  ,  "}, 770059 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 770059, :key "journals/cacm/Bergland68", :title "Numerical Analysis: A fast fourier transform algorithm for real-valued series.", :abstract "A new procedure is presented for calculating the complex, discrete Fourier transform of real-valued time series. This procedure is described for an example where the number of points in the series is an integral power of two. This algorithm preserves the order and symmetry of the Cooley-Tukey fast Fourier transform algorithm while effecting the two-to-one reduction in computation and storage which can be achieved when the series is real. Also discussed are hardware and software implementations of the algorithm which perform only (N/4) log2 (N/2) complex multiply and add operations, and which require only N real storage locations in analyzing each N-point record.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 604064, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Glenn D. Bergland"}), :year 1968, :venue "Commun. ACM", :ncit 116, :string "Numerical Analysis: A fast fourier transform algorithm for real-valued series.. A new procedure is presented for calculating the complex, discrete Fourier transform of real-valued time series. This procedure is described for an example where the number of points in the series is an integral power of two. This algorithm preserves the order and symmetry of the Cooley-Tukey fast Fourier transform algorithm while effecting the two-to-one reduction in computation and storage which can be achieved when the series is real. Also discussed are hardware and software implementations of the algorithm which perform only (N/4) log2 (N/2) complex multiply and add operations, and which require only N real storage locations in analyzing each N-point record.", :doc-id "Numerical Analysis: A fast fourier transform algorithm for real-valued series. 1968  "}, 1045387 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1045387, :key "journals/prl/OirrakDA02", :title "Affine invariant descriptors using Fourier series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 664415, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Ahmed El Oirrak"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 488426, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mohamed Daoudi"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 321694, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Driss Aboutajdine"}), :year 2002, :venue "Pattern Recognition Letters", :ncit 43, :string "Affine invariant descriptors using Fourier series.. ", :doc-id "Affine invariant descriptors using Fourier series. 2002  ,  ,  "}, 449483 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 449483, :key "conf/issac/Miller89", :title "A Program Generator for Efficient Evaluation of Fourier Series.", :abstract "Many fields require the evaluation of large multi-variate Fourier series, but the naive method of calling sine and cosine for each term can be prohibitive where computing resources are constrained or the series are extremely large (30,000 terms). Although the number of such calls can be reduced by using trigonometric identities, such a reduction is usually not possible by hand. Indeed, even when it is carried out by computer, care must be taken to generate compact programs and avoid generating large numbers of intermediate terms. We describe here an algorithm for automatically generating very efficient Fortran programs directly from the mathematical description of the series to be evaluated. The resulting Fortran programs are 5-7 times faster than the naive version and sometimes significantly more compact.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 337385, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "B. R. Miller"}), :year 1989, :venue "ISSAC", :ncit 3, :string "A Program Generator for Efficient Evaluation of Fourier Series.. Many fields require the evaluation of large multi-variate Fourier series, but the naive method of calling sine and cosine for each term can be prohibitive where computing resources are constrained or the series are extremely large (30,000 terms). Although the number of such calls can be reduced by using trigonometric identities, such a reduction is usually not possible by hand. Indeed, even when it is carried out by computer, care must be taken to generate compact programs and avoid generating large numbers of intermediate terms. We describe here an algorithm for automatically generating very efficient Fortran programs directly from the mathematical description of the series to be evaluated. The resulting Fortran programs are 5-7 times faster than the naive version and sometimes significantly more compact.", :doc-id "A Program Generator for Efficient Evaluation of Fourier Series. 1989  "}, 774316 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 774316, :key "journals/cacm/Mifsud63c", :title "Algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 198160, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Charles J. Mifsud"}), :year 1963, :venue "Commun. ACM", :ncit 2, :string "Algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation.. ", :doc-id "Algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation. 1963  "}, 1102028 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1102028, :key "journals/tip/TabeiU92", :title "Backprojection by upsampled Fourier series expansion and interpolated FFT.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 371931, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Makoto Tabei"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 99397, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mitsuhiro Ueda"}), :year 1992, :venue "IEEE Transactions on Image Processing", :ncit 0, :string "Backprojection by upsampled Fourier series expansion and interpolated FFT.. ", :doc-id "Backprojection by upsampled Fourier series expansion and interpolated FFT. 1992  ,  "}, 958828 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 958828, :key "journals/jat/Weisz05", :title "Marcinkiewicz multiplier theorem and the Sunouchi operator for Ciesielski-Fourier series.", :abstract "Some classical results due to Marcinkiewicz, Littlewood and Paley are proved for the Ciesielski-Fourier series. The Marcinkiewicz multiplier theorem is obtained for Lp spaces and extended to Hardy spaces. The boundedness of the Sunouchi operator on Lp and Hardy spaces is also investigated.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1500098, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Ferenc Weisz"}), :year 2005, :venue "Journal of Approximation Theory", :ncit 0, :string "Marcinkiewicz multiplier theorem and the Sunouchi operator for Ciesielski-Fourier series.. Some classical results due to Marcinkiewicz, Littlewood and Paley are proved for the Ciesielski-Fourier series. The Marcinkiewicz multiplier theorem is obtained for Lp spaces and extended to Hardy spaces. The boundedness of the Sunouchi operator on Lp and Hardy spaces is also investigated.", :doc-id "Marcinkiewicz multiplier theorem and the Sunouchi operator for Ciesielski-Fourier series. 2005  "}, 628236 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 628236, :key "conf/time/KawagoeU02", :title "A Similarity Search Method of Time Series Data with Combination of Fourier and Wavelet Transforms.", :abstract "Recently, time-series data, such as stock exchange rates and weather data, has widely been used in many fields. Similarity search of time-series data is important because it is useful for predicting data changes and for searching for common sources. In this paper, we propose a new similarity search method of time-series data using both Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT) and Wavelet Transform (WT). A method of reducing time-series indexing size, using a correlation coefficient, is also presented.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 365196, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Kyoji Kawagoe"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1059709, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Tomohiro Ueda"}), :year 2002, :venue "TIME", :ncit 19, :string "A Similarity Search Method of Time Series Data with Combination of Fourier and Wavelet Transforms.. Recently, time-series data, such as stock exchange rates and weather data, has widely been used in many fields. Similarity search of time-series data is important because it is useful for predicting data changes and for searching for common sources. In this paper, we propose a new similarity search method of time-series data using both Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT) and Wavelet Transform (WT). A method of reducing time-series indexing size, using a correlation coefficient, is also presented.", :doc-id "A Similarity Search Method of Time Series Data with Combination of Fourier and Wavelet Transforms. 2002  ,  "}, 2929516 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 2929516, :key "journals/amc/Sarigol10", :title "On the local properties of factored Fourier series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1595886, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mehmet Ali Sarigöl"}), :year 2010, :venue "Applied Mathematics and Computation", :ncit 2, :string "On the local properties of factored Fourier series.. ", :doc-id "On the local properties of factored Fourier series. 2010  "}, 3075309 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3075309, :key "journals/moc/Olver09", :title "On the convergence rate of a modified Fourier series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1017637, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sheehan Olver"}), :year 2009, :venue "Math. Comput.", :ncit 17, :string "On the convergence rate of a modified Fourier series.. ", :doc-id "On the convergence rate of a modified Fourier series. 2009  "}, 2925869 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 2925869, :key "journals/mlq/Moser10", :title "On the convergence of Fourier series of computable Lebesgue integrable functions.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1454974, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Philippe Moser"}), :year 2010, :venue "Math. Log. Q.", :ncit 1, :string "On the convergence of Fourier series of computable Lebesgue integrable functions.. ", :doc-id "On the convergence of Fourier series of computable Lebesgue integrable functions. 2010  "}, 3554765 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3554765, :key "journals/ijmmsc/NavasRV12", :title "Old and New Identities for Bernoulli Polynomials via Fourier Series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1625467, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Luis M. Navas"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 294352, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Francisco J. Ruiz"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 67452, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Juan Luis Varona"}), :year 2012, :venue "Int. J. Math. Mathematical Sciences", :ncit 0, :string "Old and New Identities for Bernoulli Polynomials via Fourier Series.. ", :doc-id "Old and New Identities for Bernoulli Polynomials via Fourier Series. 2012  ,  ,  "}, 776909 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 776909, :key "journals/cacm/Wells62", :title "Algorithm 128: Summation of Fourier series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 376978, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "M. Wells"}), :year 1962, :venue "Commun. ACM", :ncit 0, :string "Algorithm 128: Summation of Fourier series.. ", :doc-id "Algorithm 128: Summation of Fourier series. 1962  "}, 1045389 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1045389, :key "journals/prl/OirrakDA03", :title "Affine invariant descriptors for color images using Fourier series.", :abstract "In this paper we use Fourier series to produce normalized coefficients for color images which are invariant under any affine transformation. In the reference [Pattern Recogn. Lett., 23 (2002) 1109], the proposed algorithm is developed to be applied to shape extracted from binary images, thus it is used to discriminate objects based only on their shape similarity. That means that it is unable to discriminate two objects with the same shape but different colors and textures. It is known also that the shape extraction is not an easy and well-solved problem. The present paper addresses the problem of constructing invariants and motion estimates using both shape and color informations. The quantitative evaluation of the proposed approach shows promising results.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 664415, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Ahmed El Oirrak"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 488426, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mohamed Daoudi"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 321694, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Driss Aboutajdine"}), :year 2003, :venue "Pattern Recognition Letters", :ncit 12, :string "Affine invariant descriptors for color images using Fourier series.. In this paper we use Fourier series to produce normalized coefficients for color images which are invariant under any affine transformation. In the reference [Pattern Recogn. Lett., 23 (2002) 1109], the proposed algorithm is developed to be applied to shape extracted from binary images, thus it is used to discriminate objects based only on their shape similarity. That means that it is unable to discriminate two objects with the same shape but different colors and textures. It is known also that the shape extraction is not an easy and well-solved problem. The present paper addresses the problem of constructing invariants and motion estimates using both shape and color informations. The quantitative evaluation of the proposed approach shows promising results.", :doc-id "Affine invariant descriptors for color images using Fourier series. 2003  ,  ,  "}, 1331662 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1331662, :key "conf/ijcci/Halawa09", :title "Training Fourier Series Neural Networks to Map Closed Curves.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 964148, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Krzysztof Halawa"}), :year 2009, :venue "IJCCI", :ncit 0, :string "Training Fourier Series Neural Networks to Map Closed Curves.. ", :doc-id "Training Fourier Series Neural Networks to Map Closed Curves. 2009  "}, 3115694 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3115694, :key "journals/jcam/CiaurriV09", :title "The surprising almost everywhere convergence of Fourier-Neumann series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 231571, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Óscar Ciaurri"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 293298, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Juan L. Varona"}), :year 2009, :venue "J. Computational Applied Mathematics", :ncit 0, :string "The surprising almost everywhere convergence of Fourier-Neumann series.. ", :doc-id "The surprising almost everywhere convergence of Fourier-Neumann series. 2009  ,  "}, 775854 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 775854, :key "journals/cacm/Schubert63b", :title "Remark on algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1151968, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "George R. Schubert"}), :year 1963, :venue "Commun. ACM", :ncit 0, :string "Remark on algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation.. ", :doc-id "Remark on algorithm 157: Fourier series approximation. 1963  "}, 3453710 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3453710, :key "journals/asc/ChaquetC12", :title "Solving differential equations with Fourier series and Evolution Strategies.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1611200, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "José M. Chaquet"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 497883, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Enrique J. Carmona"}), :year 2012, :venue "Appl. Soft Comput.", :ncit 0, :string "Solving differential equations with Fourier series and Evolution Strategies.. ", :doc-id "Solving differential equations with Fourier series and Evolution Strategies. 2012  ,  "}, 950062 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 950062, :key "journals/jacm/Crump76", :title "Numerical Inversion of Laplace Transforms Using a Fourier Series Approximation.", :abstract "A method is presented for numerically inverting a Laplace transform that requires, in addition to the transform function itself, only sine, cosine, and exponential functions. The method is conceptually much like the method of Dubner and Abate, which approximates the inverse function by means of a Fourier cosine series. The method presented here, however, differs from theirs in two important respects. First of all, the Fourier series contains additional terms involving the sine function selected such that the error in the approximation is less than that of Dubner and Abate and such that the Fourier series approximates the inverse function on an interval of twice the length of the corresponding interval in Dubner and Abate's method. Second, there is incorporated into the method in this paper a transformation of the approximating series into one that converges very rapidly. In test problems using the method it has routinely been possible to evaluate inverse transforms with considerable accuracy over a wide range of values of the independent variable using a relatively few determinations of the Laplace transform itself.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1479748, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Kenny S. Crump"}), :year 1976, :venue "J. ACM", :ncit 443, :string "Numerical Inversion of Laplace Transforms Using a Fourier Series Approximation.. A method is presented for numerically inverting a Laplace transform that requires, in addition to the transform function itself, only sine, cosine, and exponential functions. The method is conceptually much like the method of Dubner and Abate, which approximates the inverse function by means of a Fourier cosine series. The method presented here, however, differs from theirs in two important respects. First of all, the Fourier series contains additional terms involving the sine function selected such that the error in the approximation is less than that of Dubner and Abate and such that the Fourier series approximates the inverse function on an interval of twice the length of the corresponding interval in Dubner and Abate's method. Second, there is incorporated into the method in this paper a transformation of the approximating series into one that converges very rapidly. In test problems using the method it has routinely been possible to evaluate inverse transforms with considerable accuracy over a wide range of values of the independent variable using a relatively few determinations of the Laplace transform itself.", :doc-id "Numerical Inversion of Laplace Transforms Using a Fourier Series Approximation. 1976  "}, 995182 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 995182, :key "journals/jscic/NersessianP06", :title "On a Rational Linear Approximation of Fourier Series for Smooth Functions.", :abstract "The Fourier series of a smooth function on a compact interval usually has slow convergence due to the Gibbs phenomena. A class of Fourier-Pade approximations is introduced and studied for performing a boundary correction. Additional acceleration is achieved by applying Fourier---Bernoulli scheme.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 340585, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "A. Nersessian"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 298370, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "A. Poghosyan"}), :year 2006, :venue "J. Sci. Comput.", :ncit 13, :string "On a Rational Linear Approximation of Fourier Series for Smooth Functions.. The Fourier series of a smooth function on a compact interval usually has slow convergence due to the Gibbs phenomena. A class of Fourier-Pade approximations is introduced and studied for performing a boundary correction. Additional acceleration is achieved by applying Fourier---Bernoulli scheme.", :doc-id "On a Rational Linear Approximation of Fourier Series for Smooth Functions. 2006  ,  "}, 2945839 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 2945839, :key "conf/icinco/PetricGZ10", :title "Frequency Extraction based on Adaptive Fourier Series - Application to Robotic Yoyo.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1610178, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Tadej Petric"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 966649, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Andrej Gams"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1068173, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Leon Zlajpah"}), :year 2010, :venue "ICINCO (2)", :ncit 3, :string "Frequency Extraction based on Adaptive Fourier Series - Application to Robotic Yoyo.. ", :doc-id "Frequency Extraction based on Adaptive Fourier Series - Application to Robotic Yoyo. 2010  ,  ,  "}, 1279855 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1279855, :key "journals/neco/Kottas93", :title "Training Periodic Sequences Using Fourier Series Error Criterion.", :abstract "Training a network to learn a set of periodic input/output sequences effectively makes the network learn a mapping between amplitudes and phases in Fourier space. The spectral backpropagation (SBP) training algorithm is a different way of doing this task. It measures the Fourier series components of the output error sequences and minimizes the total spectral energy as an adaptation criterion. This approach can train not only the weights but also time delays associated with the interconnects. Furthermore, the cells can have finite bandwidth via a first-order low-pass filter. Having adaptable time delays gives the SBP algorithm a powerful way to control the phase characteristics of the network.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 145570, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "James A. Kottas"}), :year 1993, :venue "Neural Computation", :ncit 1, :string "Training Periodic Sequences Using Fourier Series Error Criterion.. Training a network to learn a set of periodic input/output sequences effectively makes the network learn a mapping between amplitudes and phases in Fourier space. The spectral backpropagation (SBP) training algorithm is a different way of doing this task. It measures the Fourier series components of the output error sequences and minimizes the total spectral energy as an adaptation criterion. This approach can train not only the weights but also time delays associated with the interconn