lance control.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 391536, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Lin Yang"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1311263, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Chee-Meng Chew"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 849305, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Yu Zheng"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 405966, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Aun Neow Poo"}), :year 2010, :venue "Robotica", :ncit 3, :string "Truncated Fourier series formulation for bipedal walking balance control.. ", :doc-id "Truncated Fourier series formulation for bipedal walking balance control. 2010  ,  ,  ,  "}, 3083516 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3083516, :key "journals/amc/RhoadesOA11", :title "On the degree of approximation of functions belonging to a Lipschitz class by Hausdorff means of its fourier series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 481098, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "B. E. Rhoades"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14125625, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Kevser Ozkoklu"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14125626, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Inci Albayrak"}), :year 2011, :venue "Applied Mathematics and Computation", :ncit 14, :string "On the degree of approximation of functions belonging to a Lipschitz class by Hausdorff means of its fourier series.. ", :doc-id "On the degree of approximation of functions belonging to a Lipschitz class by Hausdorff means of its fourier series. 2011  ,  ,  "}, 2888028 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 2888028, :key "journals/eaai/Mills06", :title "Novel method and system for pattern recognition and processing using data encoded as Fourier series in Fourier space.", :abstract "A method and system for pattern recognition and processing is reported that has a data structure and theoretical basis that are unique. This novel approach anticipates the signal processing action of an ensemble of neurons as a unit and intends to simulate aspects of brain that give rise to capabilities such as intelligence, pattern recognition, and reasoning that have not been reproduced with past approaches such as neural networks that are based individual simulated ''neuronal units.'' Information representative of physical characteristics or representations of physical characteristics is transformed into a Fourier series in Fourier space within an input context of the physical characteristics that is encoded in time as delays corresponding to modulation of the Fourier series at corresponding frequencies. Associations are formed between Fourier series by filtering the Fourier series and by using a spectral similarity between the filtered Fourier series to determine the association based on Poissonian probability. The associated Fourier series are added to form strings of Fourier series. Each string is ordered by filtering it with multiple selected filters to form multiple time order formatted subset Fourier series, and by establishing the order through associations with one or more initially ordered strings to form an ordered string. Associations are formed between the ordered strings to form complex ordered strings that relate similar items of interest. The components of the system based on the algorithm are active based on probability using weighting factors based on activation rates.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1276343, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Randell L. Mills"}), :year 2006, :venue "Eng. Appl. of AI", :ncit 0, :string "Novel method and system for pattern recognition and processing using data encoded as Fourier series in Fourier space.. A method and system for pattern recognition and processing is reported that has a data structure and theoretical basis that are unique. This novel approach anticipates the signal processing action of an ensemble of neurons as a unit and intends to simulate aspects of brain that give rise to capabilities such as intelligence, pattern recognition, and reasoning that have not been reproduced with past approaches such as neural networks that are based individual simulated ''neuronal units.'' Information representative of physical characteristics or representations of physical characteristics is transformed into a Fourier series in Fourier space within an input context of the physical characteristics that is encoded in time as delays corresponding to modulation of the Fourier series at corresponding frequencies. Associations are formed between Fourier series by filtering the Fourier series and by using a spectral similarity between the filtered Fourier series to determine the association based on Poissonian probability. The associated Fourier series are added to form strings of Fourier series. Each string is ordered by filtering it with multiple selected filters to form multiple time order formatted subset Fourier series, and by establishing the order through associations with one or more initially ordered strings to form an ordered string. Associations are formed between the ordered strings to form complex ordered strings that relate similar items of interest. The components of the system based on the algorithm are active based on probability using weighting factors based on activation rates.", :doc-id "Novel method and system for pattern recognition and processing using data encoded as Fourier series in Fourier space. 2006  "}, 3355228 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3355228, :key "journals/automatica/Partington91", :title "Approximation of delay systems by fourier-laguerre series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 497499, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Jonathan R. Partington"}), :year 1991, :venue "Automatica", :ncit 48, :string "Approximation of delay systems by fourier-laguerre series.. ", :doc-id "Approximation of delay systems by fourier-laguerre series. 1991  "}, 1339164 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 1339164, :key "journals/jmiv/Grigoryan06", :title "Representation of the Fourier Transform by Fourier Series.", :abstract "The analysis of the mathematical structure of the integral Fourier transform shows that the transform can be split and represented by certain sets of frequencies as coefficients of Fourier series of periodic functions in the interval $$[0,2\\pi)$$ . In this paper we describe such periodic functions for the one- and two-dimensional Fourier transforms. The approximation of the inverse Fourier transform by periodic functions is described. The application of the new representation is considered for the discrete Fourier transform, when the transform is split into a set of short and separable 1-D transforms, and the discrete signal is represented as a set of short signals. Properties of such representation, which is called the paired representation, are considered and the basis paired functions are described. An effective application of new forms of representation of a two-dimensional image by splitting-signals is described for image enhancement. It is shown that by processing only one splitting-signal, one can achieve an enhancement that may exceed results of traditional methods of image enhancement.", :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 888666, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Artyom M. Grigoryan"}), :year 2006, :venue "Journal of Mathematical Imaging and Vision", :ncit 5, :string "Representation of the Fourier Transform by Fourier Series.. The analysis of the mathematical structure of the integral Fourier transform shows that the transform can be split and represented by certain sets of frequencies as coefficients of Fourier series of periodic functions in the interval $$[0,2\\pi)$$ . In this paper we describe such periodic functions for the one- and two-dimensional Fourier transforms. The approximation of the inverse Fourier transform by periodic functions is described. The application of the new representation is considered for the discrete Fourier transform, when the transform is split into a set of short and separable 1-D transforms, and the discrete signal is represented as a set of short signals. Properties of such representation, which is called the paired representation, are considered and the basis paired functions are described. An effective application of new forms of representation of a two-dimensional image by splitting-signals is described for image enhancement. It is shown that by processing only one splitting-signal, one can achieve an enhancement that may exceed results of traditional methods of image enhancement.", :doc-id "Representation of the Fourier Transform by Fourier Series. 2006  "}, 3771677 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3771677, :key "conf/robio/HaiderAW12", :title "On evolving a dynamic bipedal walk using Partial Fourier Series.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 35399, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sajjad Haider"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14447911, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Shaukat R. Abidi"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 108272, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Mary-Anne Williams"}), :year 2012, :venue "ROBIO", :ncit 0, :string "On evolving a dynamic bipedal walk using Partial Fourier Series.. ", :doc-id "On evolving a dynamic bipedal walk using Partial Fourier Series. 2012  ,  ,  "}, 3393149 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3393149, :key "journals/amc/FaydaogluY12", :title "Applications of finite and infinite Fourier series in heat processes with impulse data.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14274955, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "S. Faydaoglu"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 907798, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "V. G. Yakhno"}), :year 2012, :venue "Applied Mathematics and Computation", :ncit 0, :string "Applications of finite and infinite Fourier series in heat processes with impulse data.. ", :doc-id "Applications of finite and i